		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've thought about this too.  The way I envisioned it, rather than connecting to the expansion port, the Raspberry Pi would be housed inside the game cartridge and interface with its circuit board. <br /><br />If you remove enough components from the Raspberry Pi it will fit in a NES cart along with a USB wireless adapter and lithium-ion battery.

		

		</td>
