		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Basically it won't be seamless for existing games. You could code new applications that are aware of the issues and function correctly.<br /><br />Also, it's not just the Raspberry Pi you can do this with. There's an excellent Arduino Ethernet board I've worked with in the past. You can also do this with an NES to PC interface. Also, it seems like there was a project a while back that did offer internet connectivity to the NES.

		

		</td>
